## Section 34: State Management Patterns

### 34.1 Local vs Global State

**Local State (useState)**:
```tsx
// Use for:
// - UI state (open/closed, selected)
// - Form inputs
// - Component-specific data

const [isOpen, setIsOpen] = useState(false);
const [formData, setFormData] = useState({});
const [loading, setLoading] = useState(false);
```

**Global State (Redux/Context)**:
```tsx
// Use for:
// - User authentication
// - User profile data
// - App-wide settings
// - Shared data across routes

const { user, isAuthenticated } = useSelector(state => state.auth);
const dispatch = useDispatch();
```

### 34.2 Data Fetching Pattern

```tsx
const useTransactions = (filters) => {
  const [data, setData] = useState([]);
  const [loading, setLoading] = useState(true);
  const [error, setError] = useState(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    const fetchData = async () => {
      setLoading(true);
      setError(null);

      try {
        const response = await api.getTransactions(filters);
        setData(response.data);
      } catch (err) {
        setError(err);
      } finally {
        setLoading(false);
      }
    };

    fetchData();
  }, [filters]);

  return { data, loading, error };
};
```

